us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.tools

Class EuclidFrameTestTools

  • java.lang.Object
    • us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.tools.EuclidFrameTestTools

  • public class EuclidFrameTestTools
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides the tools to perform a variety of assertions on frame geometry types.

      • assertRotationFrameVectorEquals

        @Deprecated
public static void assertRotationFrameVectorEquals(FrameVector3DReadOnly expected,
                                                                FrameVector3DReadOnly actual,
                                                                double epsilon)
        Deprecated. Use assertRotationFrameVectorGeometricallyEquals(FrameVector3DReadOnly, FrameVector3DReadOnly, double) instead. This method will be removed in a future version.
        Asserts on a per component basis that the two rotation frame vectors are equal to an epsilon.

        The method returns true for angles such as: actualAngle = expectedAngle +/- 2.0 * Math.PI.

        Note: the two arguments are considered to be equal if they are both equal to null.

        Parameters:
        expected - the expected rotation frame vector. Not modified.
        actual - the actual rotation frame vector. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance to use.
        Throws:
        java.lang.AssertionError - if the two rotation vectors are not equal or not expressed in the same reference frame. If only one of the arguments is equal to null.
